<L>__{int shawshank hearings room day (1947)}
<A>__{red enters, removes his cap and waits by the chair.}
<D>__{man #1 sit.}
<A>__{red sits, tries not to slouch. the chair is uncomfortable.}
<D>__{man #2 we see by your file you've served twenty years of a life sentence. man #3 you feel you've been rehabilitated?}
<C>__{red}
<D>__{yes, sir. absolutely. i've learned my lesson. i can honestly say i'm a changed man. i'm no longer a danger to society. that's the god's honest truth. no doubt about it.}
<A>__{the men just stare at him. one stifles a yawn. closeup parole form a big rubber stamp slams down: "rejected" in red ink.}
